726424f-a.title: Queens: Corona Avenue - 111th Street
726424f-a.text:
Corona Avenue (Trolley thereon) east from 111th Street.
The two story brick buildin at the left foreground is on the S.E.
corner of Gorona Avenue and Saultell Street.
May 30, 1938.
P.L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

726423f-a.title: Queens: Corona Avenue - 111th Street
726423f-a.text:
Corona Avenue, east side, at 111th Street, showing a
diner which has been especially erected here to serve the
visitors to the Neww York Worldts Fair of 1939-40.
June 23, 1940
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS

725790f-a.title: Queens: 111th Street - Corona Avenue
725790f-a.text:
111th Street, at Corona Avenue. The frame house is on
the east side of 111th Street, Corona Avenue being in the
foreground with tracks thereon.
P. L. Sperr  April 19, 1936
No REPRODUCTIONS
